# üêû bug report

### Affected Package
    "@angular/core": "~9.0.5",

### Is this a regression?
Yes, this worked in Angular 8.  It also works in Angular 9 if you turn off Ivy.

### Description
Registering a callback with ViewRef.onDestroy will result in the following error when the component is destroyed:

ERROR TypeError: tCleanup[i].call is not a function

## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction
I cannot seem to update the packages in stackblitz.com, so here is a short snippet:

```
import { NgModule, Component, ChangeDetectorRef, ViewRef } from '@angular/core';
import { BrowserModule } from '@angular/platform-browser';

/** AppComponent */
@Component({
  selector: 'app-root',
  template: `
    <h3>Click this button and look for red in console</h3>
    <button (click)="show=!show">Toggle</button>
    <br />
    <app-dummy *ngIf="show"></app-dummy>
`
})
export class AppComponent { show = true; }

/** DummyComponent */
@Component({ selector: 'app-dummy', template: `<h1>Hello World</h1>` })
export class DummyComponent {
  constructor(cdr: ChangeDetectorRef) {
    (cdr as ViewRef).onDestroy(() => alert('Good bye!'));
  }
}

/** AppModule */
@NgModule({
  declarations: [ AppComponent, DummyComponent ],
  imports: [ BrowserModule ],
  providers: [],
  bootstrap: [AppComponent]
})
export class AppModule { }
```

## üî• Exception or Error
<pre><code>
ERROR TypeError: tCleanup[i].call is not a function
</code></pre>

