# üêû bug report

### Affected Package
Angular 9.0.7 and Angular 9.1.0-rc.0

### Is this a regression?
Yes, lazy components were working in the first versions of 9.0.0, now with 9.0.5-9.0.7 the bug appeared.

### Description

When loading a component lazy with the resolveComponentFactory() described in different [Tutorials](https://johnpapa.net/angular-9-lazy-loading-components/) the component don't inherit the CommonModule or any other Dependencies from the parent Module where they are loaded.

## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction

In this example I reduced it to two child components. the first is declared in app.module and is loading just fine. the second is loaded without any previous declarations and should therefore be lazy loaded.

https://stackblitz.com/edit/angular-9-0-7-lazy-component

## üî• Exception or Error
I tried to reproduce with stackblitz but there I get different error: 

```bash
No component factory found for Child2Component. Did you add it to @NgModule.entryComponents?
```

In my local environment this error is not appearing but I get rather the following error messages, which is the error I'm referring to:

```bash
error NG8002: Can't bind to 'ngSwitch' since it isn't a known property of 'ul'.
3   [ngSwitch]="item.switch"
```

In my project I use different pipes and directives that are shared via a SharedModule and is loaded to the parent module where the lazy components are attached. All these dependencies are not available in the lazy child components. Only empty components with no other dependencies are working.


